Zelnaks are exp cash cows in Dawnshroud peaks. <br>
<br>
If your pets can handle them just pull kill as many as you can.  Lightning crawler bug things over by seru city may be easier.  <br>
<br>
I took my lvl 37 warrior to lvl 44 in dawn shroud with out pl'ing just a cleric warrior and rouge group most of the time and we ate the zells like mad and lvl'ed like crazy.  i think i made 37-40 in 20 hours (group sizes varried) and through 40 in about 6 hours the rest is a blur 41-44 didnt take long is all i know,  also i was able to solo there with my warrior just using bandages for very little down time, Just killing zells (aka zelniaks)  save the meat and fat they drop for quests. <br>
<br>
the other hot exp zone i found is TM where the vampire camps are, but not doing vampires.  finished 44 and half way through 45 in about 8 hours their so far.  The Sonic wolfs are the exp cash cows there.  could solo them too but it takes longer to bandage from say 10percent life to 50percent hehe.<br>
<br>
would suggest not killing the moon men because they are not kos to most and its nice to not have to worry about them.  <br>
<br>
The key to a Mage in these zones is that if a warrior can solo these things then they dont have many hitpoints and should be taken down fairly well with some old mage nukage while pet tanks stratagy. <br>
<br>
Unfortunately i can only speculate because i dont have exp in these zones at lvl 36 as a mage.   Currently cranking my cleric and enchanter through lvl's in these zones as well.  You basically can power lvl yourself with a clean efficiant small group (3-4) that knows what they are doing,  The key is to murders the easy but good exp mobs fast and in large numbers.   Harder mobs like wolfs are doable but will be a drain on mana and health and slow you way down. <br>
<br>
The draw back is that this is exp grinding and gets dead boaring grouped or not.  depends on how bad you want the exp, i guess. <br>
<br>
I've capped a few blue off the wolfs and Rock grabbers in the dawnshroud zone with my mage from lvl's 55-56 as well.   typical mage soloing tactics.  i'm sure a 51'st lvl mage could do much better here on wolfs and up. <br>
<br>
Warning i had to chain cast pets on a blue mushroom at lvl 56.  gave nice exp but is a nasty sk mob and will cast fear on you and pet, and or snare root.  the only way to play safe here is to learn the zone and the train patterns and work in areas that are relatively safe.  The monster pathing around the zone is very tight and their are few places you can go with out wandering mobs all over you.  the nice thing is Zells are non kos unless in wolf form. <br>
<br>
Hint stay on the Seru zone side  of zone untill you can take out wolfs easy.<br>
